   307→<section class="format-section" id="format">
   308→  <div class="container">
   309→    <div class="section-label fade-up">The format</div>
   310→    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">10 hours of focused building.</h2>
   311→    <p class="section-sub fade-up">No slides. No pitch decks at the start. You arrive, you form a team, you build. At the end, you demo a working product to the judges and your peers.</p>
   312→
   313→    <div class="timeline fade-up">
   314→      <div class="timeline-item">
   315→        <div class="timeline-time">10:00</div>
   316→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   317→        <div class="timeline-content">
   318→          <h3>Kickoff &amp; theme reveal</h3>
   319→          <p>The technical theme or problem space is announced. Team up, pick your angle, define your scope. You have 30 minutes to align — then you build.</p>
   320→        </div>
   321→      </div>
   322→      <div class="timeline-item">
   323→        <div class="timeline-time">10:30</div>
   324→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   325→        <div class="timeline-content">
   326→          <h3>Building begins</h3>
   327→          <p>Heads down. Real code, real infrastructure, real product. Experienced mentors are in the room to unblock you when you're stuck.</p>
   328→        </div>
   329→      </div>
   330→      <div class="timeline-item">
   331→        <div class="timeline-time">13:00</div>
   332→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   333→        <div class="timeline-content">
   334→          <h3>Lunch + mid-day check-in</h3>
   335→          <p>Break, eat, recalibrate. Optional 5-minute mid-day check-ins with a mentor if you've hit a wall or want to pressure-test your approach.</p>
   336→        </div>
   337→      </div>
   338→      <div class="timeline-item">
   339→        <div class="timeline-time">14:00</div>
   340→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   341→        <div class="timeline-content">
   342→          <h3>Back to building</h3>
   343→          <p>Afternoon block. Focus on making it work end-to-end, not just look good. A working demo matters more than a polished UI.</p>
   344→        </div>
   345→      </div>
   346→      <div class="timeline-item">
   347→        <div class="timeline-time">18:00</div>
   348→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   349→        <div class="timeline-content">
   350→          <h3>Freeze + prep demos</h3>
   351→          <p>Code freeze. Two hours to prep your demo — no new features, just make it presentable and tell the story clearly.</p>
   352→        </div>
   353→      </div>
   354→      <div class="timeline-item">
   355→        <div class="timeline-time">19:00</div>
   356→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   357→        <div class="timeline-content">
   358→          <h3>Demo + pitches</h3>
   359→          <p>Each team gets 5 minutes. Live demo, one slide max. Mentors and peers ask real questions. The best teams get follow-up conversations, not just a prize.</p>
   360→        </div>
   361→      </div>
   362→      <div class="timeline-item">
   363→        <div class="timeline-time">20:00</div>
   364→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   365→        <div class="timeline-content">
   366→          <h3>Awards + networking</h3>
   367→          <p>Prizes, credits, and introductions. More importantly: the people in this room are who you want to know.</p>
   368→        </div>
   369→      </div>
